    "what_description": "Galium \u00d7 himmelbaurianum is a hybrid plant species within the Rubiaceae family. It is a perennial herb with erect stems, typically growing 10-20 cm tall, and has 4-angled, glabrous or pubescent stems with leafy nodes. The leaves are ovate to lanceolate, 1-3 cm long, and have an obtuse to acute apex, with 3-5 pairs of lateral veins. Inflorescences are cymose, with 2-5 flowers, and the corolla is rotate, 2-3 mm in diameter, with a 4-lobed lip and a 2-lobed upper lip. Flowers are white to pinkish, with a yellow or greenish center.",
